  "prompt": "How can you determine the chemical formula for iodine propanone?",
  "response": "To determine the chemical formula for iodine propanone, you need to understand its structure and composition. Iodine propanone is an organic compound consisting of a propanone molecule (also known as acetone) with an iodine substituent.\n\n1. **Propanone (Acetone) Structure:**\n   - Propanone is a three-carbon ketone.\n   - Its chemical formula is \\( C_3H_6O \\).\n   - Structural formula: \\( CH_3COCH_3 \\).\n\n2. **Substitution of Iodine:**\n   - Iodine can replace one of the hydrogen atoms in the propanone molecule.\n\nGiven a typical substitution reaction, iodine replaces one of the hydrogen atoms on the methyl group attached to the carbonyl group. For instance, if iodine replaces a hydrogen atom on one of the CH3 groups:\n\n\\[ Iodine Propanone: CH_2ICH_3COCH_3 \\]\n\nTherefore, actually, you get a molecule with iodine substituent at a specific position.\n\nFor the simplest structure where iodine replaces one hydrogen atom on the propanone:\n\n- The structural formula could be: \\( CH_3COCH_2I \\).\n- This substitution position is typically referred to as 2-iodopropanone.\n\nTherefore, the chemical formula for iodine propanone is \\( C_3H_5IO \\).",
